{"type":"message","id":"5ddd00ad","parentId":"2e5e60c4","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:59:22.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.read:5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"agent:main:main\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"bdc7dac0-a663-4423-a2cf-f7d298398ceb\",\n    \"updatedAt\": 1772258299803,\n    \"systemSent\": true,\n    \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n    \"model\": \"kimi-k2.5\",\n    \"origin\": {\n      \"provider\": \"webchat\",\n      \"surface\": \"webchat\",\n      \"chatType\": \"direct\",\n      \"label\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"from\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"to\": \"heartbeat\"\n    },\n    \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n    \"skillsSnapshot\": {\n      \"prompt\": \"\\n\\nThe following skills provide specialized instructions for specific tasks.\\nUse the read tool to load a skill's file when the task matches its description.\\nWhen a skill file references a relative path, resolve it against the skill directory (parent of SKILL.md / dirname of the path) and use that absolute path in tool commands.\\n\\n<available_skills>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>healthcheck</name>\\n    <description>Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments. Use when a user asks for security audits, firewall/SSH/update hardening, risk posture, exposure review, OpenClaw cron scheduling for periodic checks, or version status checks on a machine running OpenClaw (laptop, workstation, Pi, VPS).</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\healthcheck\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>mcporter</name>\\n    <description>Use the mcporter CLI to list, configure, auth, and call MCP servers/tools directly (HTTP or stdio), including ad-hoc servers, config edits, and CLI/type generation.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\mcporter\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>skill-creator</name>\\n    <description>Create or update AgentSkills. Use when designing, structuring, or packaging skills with scripts, references, and assets.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\skill-creator\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>akshare-quant</name>\\n    <description>Access Chinese financial market data using AKShare library. Use when the user needs stock prices, fund data, index data, financial news, or any quantitative finance data from Chinese markets (A-shares, Hong Kong stocks, funds, indices). Provides real-time quotes, historical data, and fundamental information.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\akshare-quant\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>image-recognition</name>\\n    <description>Analyze and describe images using AI vision capabilities. Use when the user provides an image (URL, local file path, or data URI) and asks for description, analysis, OCR, or any visual understanding task. Handles automatic conversion of local file paths to accessible URLs before processing.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\image-recognition\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>playwright-browser</name>\\n    <description>Control web browsers using Playwright for web automation, scraping, and testing. Use when the user needs to automate browser actions like navigating websites, clicking elements, filling forms, taking screenshots, or extracting web data programmatically.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\playwright-browser\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>web-fetch-enhanced</name>\\n    <description>Fetch and extract content from web URLs with fallback strategies and better error handling. Use when the built-in web_fetch tool fails or when you need more control over the fetching process, custom headers, retries, or alternative extraction methods.</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\web-fetch-enhanced\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>xiaohongshu-browser</name>\\n    <description>Browse, read, post, and comment on Xiaohongshu (小红书) using the OpenClaw browser tool. Use when the user asks you去刷小红书、点帖子、看博主、发表评论或发笔记，并且可以通过 ref/snapshot 稳定操作页面。</description>\\n    <location>D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\xiaohongshu-browser\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n</available_skills>\",\n      \"skills\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"healthcheck\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"mcporter\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"skill-creator\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"akshare-quant\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"image-recognition\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"playwright-browser\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"web-fetch-enhanced\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"xiaohongshu-browser\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"resolvedSkills\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"healthcheck\",\n          \"description\": \"Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments. Use when a user asks for security audits, firewall/SSH/update hardening, risk posture, exposure review, OpenClaw cron scheduling for periodic checks, or version status checks on a machine running OpenClaw (laptop, workstation, Pi, VPS).\",\n          \"filePath\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\healthcheck\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\healthcheck\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"mcporter\",\n          \"description\": \"Use the mcporter CLI to list, configure, auth, and call MCP servers/tools directly (HTTP or stdio), including ad-hoc servers, config edits, and CLI/type generation.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\mcporter\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\mcporter\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"skill-creator\",\n          \"description\": \"Create or update AgentSkills. Use when designing, structuring, or packaging skills with scripts, references, and assets.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\skill-creator\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"D:\\\\npm-global\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\skill-creator\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"akshare-quant\",\n          \"description\": \"Access Chinese financial market data using AKShare library. Use when the user needs stock prices, fund data, index data, financial news, or any quantitative finance data from Chinese markets (A-shares, Hong Kong stocks, funds, indices). Provides real-time quotes, historical data, and fundamental information.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\akshare-quant\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"D:\\\\.openclaw\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\akshare-quant\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-workspace\",\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"image-recognition\",\n          \"description\": \"Analyze and describe images using AI vision capabilities. Use when the user provides an image (URL, local file path, or data URI) and asks for description, analysis, OCR, or any visual understanding ta